{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782642595263,"sessionID":"ses_0f239183cffepbbsaY09yKGXIN","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9KrHf4Y0TS3IXm4gG2C76a0c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\platform-capability-check.md","limit":300,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\platform-capability-check.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Platform Capability Check\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This is the agent-maintained platform capability check. Before marking a critical/high platform capability as direct, replaced, fallback, or deferred, query CangjieSkills/HarmonyOS/Cangjie API docs, HarmonyOS-Examples, or package index lookup such as `https://pkg.cangjie-lang.cn` and record the evidence in `targetCapabilitySearch`. Direct means callable from the Cangjie target; ArkTS-only or native-only declarations are discovery evidence until an already planned or existing Cangjie wrapper, FFI, or bridge is verified with target build evidence. Use cjpm/project-management docs only to configure a chosen dependency.\n6: \n7: ## Status Values\n8: \n9: `deferred`, `implemented-fallback`, `not-applicable`, `not-covered`, `planned`, `platform-replaced`, `unreviewed`, `verified-direct`\n10: \n11: ## Deferred Required Fields\n12: \n13: `targetCapabilitySearch`, `blocker`, `targetFallback`, `futureCompletionPath`\n14: \n15: ## Entries\n16: \n17: | capability id | status | phase | importance | decision | probe | capability | target API/library | strategy |\n18: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n19: | media-library-access | not-applicable | phase-04-home-history | critical | resolved-not-applicable |  | Media library and album discovery | HarmonyOS Cangjie MediaLibraryKit / ohos.file.photo_access_helper (getPhotoAccessHelper, PhotoAccessHelper.getAlbums, album/media asset APIs) exists in the current SDK, but phase-04 home/history source behavior only consumes bundled drawable resources and does not browse user albums. | Treat the phase-04 media-library requirement as a source-analysis false positive. Implement home/history images from packaged app media resources only; do not add album discovery, gallery picker, or media permission scaffolding in this phase unless later source-backed behavior proves a real user-media flow. |\n20: | file-access-and-saf | planned | phase-05-detail-cart | critical | needs-target-search |  | File access, document permissions, and share URIs |  |  |\n21: | image-viewer-gestures | planned | phase-05-detail-cart | critical | needs-target-search |  | Image viewer gestures and metadata |  |  |\n22: | localization-resources | verified-direct | phase-01-project-skeleton-resources | high | resolved-real-api |  | Localized resources and formatted strings | HarmonyOS Cangjie LocalizationKit resource model (`ohos.base.ResourceStr`, `ohos.resource.AppResource`, `ohos.resource_manager.ResourceManager`) with standard HarmonyOS `string.json`/`color.json` resources | Phase 01 migrates Android labels, start-window colors, and resource-backed UI text into HarmonyOS descriptor/resource files, with AppResource helpers for Cangjie access where needed. Batch 3 also removes hard-coded route-shell labels by routing them through `foodike_resources.cj` and `app_router.cj` before display in `bootstrap_page.cj`. |\n23: | runtime-permissions | not-applicable | phase-02-startup-session-navigation | high | resolved-not-applicable |  | Runtime permissions and protected platform access | HarmonyOS Cangjie AbilityKit permission APIs exist (`ohos.ability_access_ctrl.AtManager`, `ohos.security.permission_request_result.PermissionRequestResult`) but are not required by phase-02 startup/session/navigation source behavior. | Treat the phase-02 permission requirement as a source-analysis false positive. Do not add permission prompts or protected-access scaffolding during startup/session/navigation implementation unless later source-backed phases introduce real protected APIs. |\n24: | background-and-platform-components | platform-replaced | phase-02-startup-session-navigation | high | resolved-platform-replacement |  | Background work, services, receivers, widgets, and notifications | HarmonyOS Cangjie AbilityKit app-entry APIs (`ohos.app.ability.ui_ability.UIAbility`, `UIAbilityContext`, `Want`) plus ArkUI `Navigation`/`NavPathStack` or `Router` for in-app startup and route flow | Resolve the source Android platform component surface as a HarmonyOS platform replacement: model app startup in the target `UIAbility`/descriptor entry, keep splash-like gating inside bootstrap state before rendering the main route, and implement onboarding/home navigation using the existing ArkUI route shell instead of Android `Application`, `ComponentActivity`, and `core-splashscreen` APIs. |\n\n(End of file - total 24 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Platform Capability Check\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis is the agent-maintained platform capability check. Before marking a critical/high platform capability as direct, replaced, fallback, or deferred, query CangjieSkills/HarmonyOS/Cangjie API docs, HarmonyOS-Examples, or package index lookup such as `https://pkg.cangjie-lang.cn` and record the evidence in `targetCapabilitySearch`. Direct means callable from the Cangjie target; ArkTS-only or native-only declarations are discovery evidence until an already planned or existing Cangjie wrapper, FFI, or bridge is verified with target build evidence. Use cjpm/project-management docs only to configure a chosen dependency.\n\n## Status Values\n\n`deferred`, `implemented-fallback`, `not-applicable`, `not-covered`, `planned`, `platform-replaced`, `unreviewed`, `verified-direct`\n\n## Deferred Required Fields\n\n`targetCapabilitySearch`, `blocker`, `targetFallback`, `futureCompletionPath`\n\n## Entries\n\n| capability id | status | phase | importance | decision | probe | capability | target API/library | strategy |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| media-library-access | not-applicable | phase-04-home-history | critical | resolved-not-applicable |  | Media library and album discovery | HarmonyOS Cangjie MediaLibraryKit / ohos.file.photo_access_helper (getPhotoAccessHelper, PhotoAccessHelper.getAlbums, album/media asset APIs) exists in the current SDK, but phase-04 home/history source behavior only consumes bundled drawable resources and does not browse user albums. | Treat the phase-04 media-library requirement as a source-analysis false positive. Implement home/history images from packaged app media resources only; do not add album discovery, gallery picker, or media permission scaffolding in this phase unless later source-backed behavior proves a real user-media flow. |\n| file-access-and-saf | planned | phase-05-detail-cart | critical | needs-target-search |  | File access, document permissions, and share URIs |  |  |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\platform-capability-check.md","time":{"start":1782642595259,"end":1782642595262}},"id":"prt_f0dc755ba001MZmw6cl5JXp9Au","sessionID":"ses_0f239183cffepbbsaY09yKGXIN","messageID":"msg_f0dc72440001Mn3QGtLaMTloD2"}}
