{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782642700490,"sessionID":"ses_0f239183cffepbbsaY09yKGXIN","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_Q9kpRlVQtZKZQsz3jJFKQBj1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"$patch = '{\"schemaVersion\":1,\"purpose\":\"Resolve phase-05 platform capabilities with source-backed false-positive closures and Cangjie SDK evidence.\",\"updates\":[{\"capabilityId\":\"file-access-and-saf\",\"set\":{\"status\":\"not-applicable\",\"targetCapabilitySearch\":[\"Source inspection of phase-05 detail/cart files shows no file picker, document import/export, URI grant, or share intent implementation: RestaurantDetail.kt only renders a share icon with an empty onClick block; Cart.kt, CartItemCard.kt, MenuItemCard.kt, and RestaurantDetailCard.kt render packaged resources and local state only.\",\"Current Cangjie SDK still exposes a real share/URI path through ohos.app.ability.want Want(uri, action, entities, dataType, parameters, fds) plus URI permission constants under ohos.app.ability.want_constant.Flags, so later source-backed cross-app share/file behavior should use Want-based HarmonyOS sharing rather than a local fallback.\",\"Because the current phase source behavior has no actual file/document/share flow to preserve, treat this capability match as a phase-05 static-analysis false positive rather than implementation scope.\"],\"targetApiOrLibrary\":\"HarmonyOS Cangjie AbilityKit Want/URI APIs (`ohos.app.ability.want.Want`, `ohos.app.ability.want_constant.Flags`) exist for real cross-app URI/file sharing, but phase-05 detail/cart source behavior does not invoke them.\",\"targetStrategy\":\"Treat the phase-05 file/document/share capability as not applicable for detail/cart. Keep the phase focused on detail/cart state and packaged-resource rendering; if a later source-backed share flow is implemented, route it through HarmonyOS Want-based sharing with explicit URI permission flags instead of introducing Android SAF assumptions.\",\"tests\":[\"phase-05 source grep found no ACTION_SEND, FileProvider, ContentResolver, MediaStore, file picker, or SAF calls in app/src/main/java\",\"manual source inspection confirms RestaurantDetail.kt share IconButton has an empty onClick block and cart/detail components use only bundled resources and local UI state\"],\"sdkDeclarationEvidence\":[\"Current Cangjie SDK declares Want constructors with uri/action/entities/dataType/parameters fields in C:\\\\Users\\\\Sieger\\\\.cangjie-sdk\\\\6.0\\\\cangjie\\\\api\\\\lib\\\\linux_ohos_aarch64_cjnative\\\\ohos\\\\ohos.app.ability.want.cjo, including `Want(... uri=6String!3uri=6String!6action=5Array<6String>!8entities=6String!8dataType=7HashMap<6String13WantValueType>!10parameters=7HashMap<6Stringi>!3fds ...)` and related `Want3uri` symbols.\",\"Current Cangjie SDK also exposes URI grant constants for real share/file flows in C:\\\\Users\\\\Sieger\\\\.cangjie-sdk\\\\6.0\\\\cangjie\\\\api\\\\lib\\\\linux_ohos_aarch64_cjnative\\\\ohos\\\\ohos.app.ability.want_constant.cjo, including `FLAG_AUTH_READ_URI_PERMISSION`, `FLAG_AUTH_WRITE_URI_PERMISSION`, and `FLAG_AUTH_PERSISTABLE_URI_PERMISSION`.\"],\"cangjieCallableEvidence\":[\"Current Cangjie SDK exposes Cangjie-callable AbilityKit sharing/URI surfaces through `ohos.app.ability.want.Want` and `ohos.app.ability.want_constant.Flags`, which are the target-platform replacement path if a later source-backed share flow is needed.\"],\"discoveryOnlyEvidence\":[],\"compileProbeEvidence\":[],\"preResolutionDecision\":\"resolved-not-applicable\",\"phaseCapabilityResolution\":\"resolved-not-applicable\",\"blocker\":\"\",\"targetFallback\":\"\",\"futureCompletionPath\":\"\",\"notes\":\"Phase-05 detail/cart source behavior does not include any implemented file access, document picker, or URI sharing workflow. The share affordance is present only as an empty button handler, so closing this capability as not-applicable preserves actual source behavior instead of inventing SAF scope.\",\"capability