kt, MenuItemCard.kt, CartItemCard.kt, and Cart.kt use `painterResource`/drawable assets and local counters; no zoom state, gesture detectors, bitmap decode pipeline, metadata panel, or full-screen image viewer route exists.\",\n+          \"HarmonyOS Cangjie docs and SDK provide direct image display and image-source APIs, including ArkUI Image and ImageKit createImageSource(String), but the current source phase does not require zoom, EXIF, or metadata behavior to preserve.\",\n+          \"Because the source behavior is packaged-image display without viewer interactions, treat this capability as a phase-05 static-analysis false positive rather than adding a gesture viewer feature not present in the app.\"\n+        ],\n+        \"targetApiOrLibrary\": \"HarmonyOS Cangjie ArkUI `Image` and ImageKit `ohos.multimedia.image.createImageSource(String)` exist for real image display/processing, but phase-05 detail/cart source behavior only needs static packaged-image rendering.\",\n+        \"targetStrategy\": \"Resolve the capability as not applicable for phase-05. Implement the detail/cart visuals with normal HarmonyOS Image rendering from packaged media; do not add zoom, reset, metadata, or EXIF UI unless a later source-backed requirement proves a real image viewer flow.\",\n+        \"tests\": [\n+          \"phase-05 source grep found no zoom, EXIF, bitmap decode, gesture detector, gallery preview, or image metadata flow in app/src/main/java\",\n+          \"manual source inspection confirms detail/cart image surfaces are static resource images with no viewer state machine or gesture callbacks\"\n+        ],\n+        \"sdkDeclarationEvidence\": [\n+          \"HarmonyOS Cangjie docs index the direct ArkUI image component in harmonyos-6.1-8k/API/arkui-cj/cj-image-video-image/Image/.overview.md, confirming a callable Cangjie image-rendering surface for packaged or remote images.\",\n+          \"HarmonyOS Cangjie docs also include ImageKit `createImageSource(String)` fo