. |\n| runtime-permissions | not-applicable | phase-02-startup-session-navigation | high | resolved-not-applicable |  | Runtime permissions and protected platform access | HarmonyOS Cangjie AbilityKit permission APIs exist (`ohos.ability_access_ctrl.AtManager`, `ohos.security.permission_request_result.PermissionRequestResult`) but are not required by phase-02 startup/session/navigation source behavior. | Treat the phase-02 permission requirement as a source-analysis false positive. Do not add permission prompts or protected-access scaffolding during startup/session/navigation implementation unless later source-backed phases introduce real protected APIs. |\n| background-and-platform-components | platform-replaced | phase-02-startup-session-navigation | high | resolved-platform-replacement |  | Background work, services, receivers, widgets, and notifications | HarmonyOS Cangjie AbilityKit app-entry APIs (`ohos.app.ability.ui_ability.UIAbility`, `UIAbilityContext`, `Want`) plus ArkUI `Navigation`/`NavPathStack` or `Router` for in-app startup and route flow | Resolve the source Android platform component surface as a HarmonyOS platform replacement: model app startup in the target `UIAbility`/descriptor entry, keep splash-like gating inside bootstrap state before rendering the main route, and implement onboarding/home navigation using the existing ArkUI route shell instead of Android `Application`, `ComponentActivity`, and `core-splashscreen` APIs. |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\platform-capability-check.md","time":{"start":1782642816599,"end":1782642816605}},"id":"prt_f0dcab656001QDEX2SlP6EskgV","sessionID":"ses_0f239183cffepbbsaY09yKGXIN","messageID":"msg_f0dca99ba001jk0m2R0H8Jf5Vv"}}
